results.name: Air temperature
results.description: Objective comparative measure of hot or cold

results.name: Atmospheric pressure
results.description: The force of the unit of area exerted by air on the earth's surface

results.name: Dew point
results.description: The highest temperature at which airborne water vapor will condense to form liquid dew

results.name: Precipitation intensity
results.description: Measure of the amount of rain that falls over time

results.name: Rain
results.description: The amount of precipitation on a point on the earth's surface

results.name: Relative humidity
results.description: Ratio of the partial pressure of water vapor to the equilibrium vapor pressure of water at given temperature

results.name: Solar irradiance
results.description: Solar irradiance is the rate at which radiant power is incident on a surface per unit area of surface

results.name: Wind direction
results.description: Wind direction is reported by the direction from which it originates

results.name: Wind speed
results.description: The rate at which air is moving in a particular area
